Toast.makeText(MainActivity.this,"Successful!!",Toast.LENGTH_SHORT).show();

Toast: Displays brief messages to the user.

Toast.makeText() creates a toast with three parameters:
Context: Where to display it (e.g., MainActivity.this).
Text: Message to show (e.g., "Successful!!").
Duration: How long it lasts:
Toast.LENGTH_SHORT: ~2 seconds.
Toast.LENGTH_LONG: ~3.5 seconds.
Call show() to display the toast.


onCreate(): This method is called when the activity is first created.
EdgeToEdge: Ensures the UI is displayed edge-to-edge on the screen.
setContentView(R.layout.activity_main): Specifies the layout file activity_main.xml to define the activity's UI elements.
